latestPosts.caption:
Mondays are for Slow Flow🧘🏽‍♀️

While I don’t believe life is short (it’s the longest thing we’ll ever do), I do believe it goes by quickly. 

How often do you take a moment to slow down?
 
To pause and appreciate not just the world but your body as you move through it.

Slow down. 

Even slower. 

Slow Flow isn’t about beginner movements, it’s about slowing down through each posture, it’s about focusing on your breath and alignment rather than rushing through poses. 

Slow flow is for beginner, intermediate, and advanced practitioners alike. You take what you need. 

With slow flow, you have the opportunity to take the modification that speaks to you. To advance your practice with intentionality. 

Slow Flow is not where I saw myself when I set out to teach yoga but it’s what I need and it’s what a lot of our bodies need. To slow down and to be fully present in the body and breathe.

Join me
📍Mondays at 7pm 
Triangle Rock Club-North Raleigh

Can’t wait to see you there💚

🎥: @palmandoakmedia for the amazing video

#yoga #slowlife #slowflow #fitness #fyp #raleigh

latestPosts.caption:
Yoga Teacher Graduation🤍✨

This is a big deal for me.
After 10 years, I FINALLY took a leap of faith.

I knew in college that one day I’d be here. 
One day I’d actually be a yoga teacher. 
But even still it’s hard to believe🥹

Gone now are the days of haphazardly teaching fellow college students as I yearned for them to love yoga the way I do. 

This training helped me grow in so many ways and I know it’s just the beginning. I’m excited for the next chapter in this journey, but I’ll miss what what this cohort created and shared together. All the lovely souls I’ve encountered. 

9 months of learning not just about yoga, but about myself. 

I couldn’t be more thankful for my teachers. All of them, through all stages of life and my practice, but particularly those who guided me through this training and continue to guide me.

@yoganic_bayer 
@goldenyogimaggs 
@janik.prochik 

And especially, my dear friend and mentor:

@laurenaliviaplays 

Who gave me the Sanskrit name: NAVI
“Kind to people”

I hope to spread kindness through movement💚✨

Yoga page: @nina.naviyoga
